content:
$TSLAIndia is a rather small opportunity for Tesla. Here's why. 
 
India's Total EV sales in 2024 = ~100k 
Most Dominant Company = Tata Motors (61k sales) 
Tesla sold 1.789 MM in 2024 
 
Currently, 100% tariffs apply for Tesla - making sales impossible. 
 
Tariffs can lower to 15% for Tesla, if they invest 500 million in a factory. Tesla's market share was ~6.6% in China for 2024, despite no tariffs. 
 
If we assume a 7% market share (which is generous, considering the tariffs), that would be 7,000 cars sold in 2025. 
 
No reasonable percentage of sales would makeup for the 72,542 decrease in sales from 2023 to 2024, even before you consider the more drastic decreases in Europe in 2025 so far - and the EV market slowdown. 
 
India's charging stations are negligible, 99% of the country can't afford an electric car, and each car sold would have a lower gross profit. 
 
Tesla doesn't currently have a catalyst for increasing sales in 2025, but it does have numerous paths to decreasing sales.economictimes.indiatimes.co...Bearish
